reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Dr. Smith is an excellent professor who explains complex concepts with ease. His lectures are engaging and informative.

reviews.subject: Mathematics
reviews.review: Prof. Johnson is very knowledgeable, but her classes can be a bit fast-paced. Be prepared to do a lot of self-study.

reviews.subject: Physics
reviews.review: Dr. Brown is okay, but sometimes his lectures are hard to follow. He does provide good resources though.

reviews.subject: Chemistry
reviews.review: Prof. Davis is amazing! Her labs are well-organized, and she makes sure everyone understands the material.

reviews.subject: Biology
reviews.review: Dr. Wilson is a great teacher, but sometimes his exams are tougher than expected. Pay attention in his lectures!

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: Dr. Moore’s classes are interesting, but her grading is harsh and unclear. Make sure you participate in discussions.

reviews.subject: Economics
reviews.review: Prof. Taylor knows his subject well, but he can be a bit monotone. His exams are fair, and he’s approachable for questions.

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: Dr. White is one of the best professors I’ve had. Her lectures are engaging, and she truly cares about her students.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Dr. Thompson’s classes are average. He’s knowledgeable but doesn’t make the material very exciting.

reviews.subject: Sociology
reviews.review: Prof. Garcia is insightful and offers a unique perspective on topics. Her assignments are thought-provoking.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Dr. Martinez is difficult to understand at times, and his grading can be inconsistent. His classes are challenging.

reviews.subject: English Literature
reviews.review: Dr. Anderson is passionate about literature and it shows in her teaching. Her feedback on papers is extremely helpful.

reviews.subject: Engineering
reviews.review: Dr. Hernandez is knowledgeable, but his lectures can be dry. His problem sets are tough but fair.

reviews.subject: Statistics
reviews.review: Prof. Jackson is thorough in her teaching. Her classes are structured well, but you need to keep up with the material.

reviews.subject: Business Management
reviews.review: Dr. Lewis is a fantastic professor who provides real-world examples to explain concepts. His classes are very practical.

reviews.subject: Art History
reviews.review: Dr. Walker’s lectures are detailed, but sometimes too much so. You’ll need to put in extra effort to stay on top of things.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Dr. Hall is passionate about the subject, and it reflects in his teaching. His field trips are particularly engaging.

reviews.subject: Linguistics
reviews.review: Prof. Young is outstanding! She makes complex topics accessible and encourages student participation.

reviews.subject: Anthropology
reviews.review: Dr. King’s classes are well-organized, and he is very knowledgeable. Sometimes the material can be dense.

reviews.subject: Pharmacology
reviews.review: Dr. Wright is okay, but her lectures can be hard to follow. Make sure to attend her office hours if you need help.
